**Job description**


We are looking for an experienced Business Analyst who is passionate about sustainability to join our Sustainable IT squad Wavemakers. You will support the embedding of sustainability in the way of working of approximately 8 tribes within Retail NL Tech (RNLT). For more information on Wavemakers, please check out the IT Labour Campaign website!


**About Wavemakers**


Wavemakers provides teams with the means to assess and visualize their carbon footprint, based on their code and resource usage. The squad aims to enable teams to leverage these tools and training, to effectively reduce their environmental impact while fostering a culture of sustainable IT within Rabobank. The team consists of engineers, solution architects, dedicated sustainability coaches, trainers and communicators, all happy and motivated to contribute to Rabobank’s mission: ‘Growing a better world together’.


**You and your job**


As a Business Analyst you are the link between business and IT. Your team is responsible for offering consultancy and innovative technical solutions for complex Sustainable IT challenges, covering all aspects of the DevOps lifecycle. You will gather, analyze and document the technical and business requirements of RNLT tribes, areas and individual DevOps teams, to incorporate Sustainable IT into their way of working.


With sustainability as your main focus, you need to be flexible in your thinking. Building on existing assets and coming up with “out of the box” solutions to meet a wide range of stakeholders’ needs, is highly valued.


**Together we achieve more**

You will regularly meet with stakeholders to promote your team’s offerings across the tribes. As the eyes and ears of your team, you will actively identify ways to bring innovative sustainable IT solutions to the bank. You will collaborate with the Product Owner to ensure that the team aligns its strategy and service offerings with the requirements of multiple tribes while coordinating with relevant stakeholders and initiatives across Rabobank.


Given the rapid evolution of sustainability needs and the exponential growth of new technologies and research (e.g., Generative AI, Sustainable IT), your work will be dynamic and always challenging.


**This is what we ask of you**


* Experience with facilitating user feedback and stakeholder workshops, gathering requirements, and translate them to technical specifications;
* Demonstrated strong analytical and conceptual thinking skills for assessing data, identifying sustainable IT practices and embedding these practices into the organization;
* Deep understanding of environmental and social responsibility, with relevant experience working on sustainability projects as a researcher or analyst is a pre;
* Support the product owner in the business development and align with various stakeholders (on all levels, across RNLT) to understand their needs;
* Apply various communication styles that best suit the target audience and enhance their willingness to commit to change;
* Promote and market new and existing offerings of your team in order to reach as much as teams as possible;
* Support your team with the realization of the technical solutions your team offers;
* Create and manage continuously improving consultancy and IT offerings for sustainable IT;
* A flexible mindset open to multiple viewpoints;
* Genuine interest in sustainability to inspire colleagues to incorporate sustainable IT in their way of working.

**You and your talent**


* 5+ years working experience as a Business Analyst, preferably including sustainability-related experience;
* Proficient in Scrum, Agile and DevOps methodologies, preferably with certifications;
* Excellent communication and presentation skills in English and (preferred) also in Dutch;
* Experience in managing complex stakeholder environments;
* Expertise in advanced change management, including specific frameworks and methodologies;
* Strong affinity for innovation and thinking outside the box;
* Eager to learn and adapt to new technologies.

**This is what we offer you**


* Gross monthly salary up to € 6.130,64 (scale 9)
* Thirteenth (13th) month's salary and (8%) holiday allowance;
* An Employee Benefit Budget of (11%) of your gross monthly salary to be used at your discretion. Buy extra holiday hours, add more to your pension savings or receive a monthly cash pay-out.
