We are looking for a highly experienced **Quality Mechanical Inspector / Work Supervisor.** The Inspector will report to our local full time Construction Monitoring Manager and the Engineering Team working in back office. He will closely collaborate with the Client engineers and Users.  


We are currently supporting our Client in the monitoring of the construction of a large space testing facility in Noordwijk (South Holland). The building will be one of the largest anechoic chambers in the world hosting a highly complex network of mechanical systems such as clean room ventilation, process cooling water, nitrogen cooling systems, compressed air, rain drainage, underground lines, fire protection. The Construction Company has currently completed the structure and the façades.
