* Check the work progress against the schedule;
* Act proactively with strong attitude to collaboration and problem solving.
**What are we looking for**  

* Bachelor’s Degree/ Master’s Degree in Mechanical Engineering;
* Experience of Major Engineering projects with high thermal and hydraulic complexity;
* > 5 years of experience on site in similar role;
* High School Diploma acceptable only if highly experienced;
* Knowledge of working with ASHRAE and EN Standards;
* Fluent English;
* Living or working in South Holland region or at least within 1.5 hours drive from site;
* Competent user of modern office computer systems e.g. Microsoft Teams, Excel, Word, PowerPoint;
* Good analytic and problem solving skills, team player;
* Attention to detail and a high level of accuracy in work;
* Good time management skills.



